summary: One thing I really like about the Pokemon narrative is how different Pokemon are shown at different strength levels for their...
body:
One thing I really like about the Pokemon narrative is how different Pokemon are shown at different strength levels for their individual trainers. A team might have one or two fully evolved Pokemon, a mid-level, and some unevolved Pokemon on it, and their individual strengths and weaknesses are highlighted.

Everyone grows on their own time and shows talent at their own pace and they’re still valued and cared for despite that, and anyone who doesn’t treat their Pokemon with respect if they’re weak is viewed as abhorrent and out of the norm.

blog.name: pokegodsandmissingno
blog.title: P̵o̵K̸é̴G̸o̸D̷s̸ and Frightful Things to Come?
blog.description: There is a growing desire and expectation of humans here on Earth in making full contact with PoKéMoN who are still unknown. Back in 1995, when I saw my first UPM (Unindexed Pocket Monster), I found out very quickly that other people thought you were totally crazy if you said you saw such things. The world has changed quite a bit since then when I was a child. In fact, in late 1997, a poll taken in Kanto shows that for the first time ever, more than fifty percent of residents now believe in PokéGODS's. Since then, there have been polls that put the figure at over eighty percent or more.

summary: Pokemon Quest Mobile Revenue Is $8 Million After Just One Month
title: Pokemon Quest Mobile Revenue Is $8 Million After Just One Month
body:
Pokemon Quest Mobile Revenue Is $8 Million After Just One Month

It seems as though Pokemon Questis another free to play title which is raking in the cash for the Pokemon Company. The game initially arrived on the Nintendo Switch but shortly afterwards the mobile version was released. Sensor Tower is reporting that in just one month it has achieved a revenue stream of $8 million. Something that secures its status as a hit. Here’s more details and statistics…
